# {{philosophy}} A type of argument proposed by a number of [[philosophers]], including [[w:Anselm_of_Canterbury|St. Anselm]] and [[w:René_Descartes|Descartes]], which maintains that the [[existence]] of [[God]] can be deduced from an [[analysis]] of the [[concept]] of God.

